{
  "topicId": "m7-t2",
  "title": "Talking about daily programs and habits",
  "dialect": "levantine",
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Waking Up"
        },
        "text": "To talk about waking up, you can use the verbs بفيق (bfi') or بصحى (bsahha) in Levantine Arabic. Both mean 'I wake up' or 'I get up'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا بفيق بكير كل يوم.",
            "english": "I wake up early every day.",
            "transliteration": "Ana bfi' bakkeer kull yōm."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هي بتصحى متأخر.",
            "english": "She wakes up late.",
            "transliteration": "Hiyye btsaḥha mta'akhkher."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Eating Meals"
        },
        "text": "Here are common verbs for eating breakfast, lunch, and dinner. These are conjugated forms for 'I'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا بفطر الساعة 7.",
            "english": "I have breakfast at 7 o'clock.",
            "transliteration": "Ana baftor is-saa'a sab'a."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "نحنا منتغدى بالبيت.",
            "english": "We have lunch at home.",
            "transliteration": "Niḥna mintghadda bil-bait."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هم بيتعشوا مع عيلتهم.",
            "english": "They have dinner with their family.",
            "transliteration": "Humma byit'ashshu ma' 'aylathom."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Going to Work or School"
        },
        "text": "To say 'I go to work' or 'I go to school', use the verb بروح (barooḥ - I go) followed by the preposition عَ (a' - to/at) and the place.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا بروح ع الشغل الصبح.",
            "english": "I go to work in the morning.",
            "transliteration": "Ana barooḥ a'sh-shughl iṣ-ṣubḥ."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هي بتروح ع المدرسة بالباص.",
            "english": "She goes to school by bus.",
            "transliteration": "Hiyye batrooḥ a'l-madrasa bil-bass."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "أنا بفيق بكير وبفطر.",
        "english": "I wake up early and have breakfast.",
        "transliteration": "Ana bfi' bakkeer w baftor."
      },
      "context": "Using 'I wake up' and 'I have breakfast'."
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "هو بروح ع الشغل كل يوم.",
        "english": "He goes to work every day.",
        "transliteration": "Huwa barooḥ a'sh-shughl kull yōm."
      },
      "context": "Using 'he goes' and 'to work'."
    },
