    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Showering and Sleeping"
        },
        "text": "Two more essential daily activities are showering and sleeping. Use بتحمم (bataḥammam - I shower) and بنام (banām - I sleep).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا بتحمم كل يوم الصبح.",
            "english": "I shower every morning.",
            "transliteration": "Ana bataḥammam kull yōm iṣ-ṣubḥ."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هو بينام الساعة عشرة.",
            "english": "He sleeps at 10 o'clock.",
            "transliteration": "Huwa benām is-saa'a 'ashara."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Expressing Frequency: Always and Usually"
        },
        "text": "To describe how often you do something, use دايماً (dayman - always) and عادةً ('aadatan - usually). These words usually come before the verb.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا دايماً بفيق بكير.",
            "english": "I always wake up early.",
            "transliteration": "Ana dayman bfi' bakkeer."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هي عادةً بتطبخ الغدا.",
            "english": "She usually cooks lunch.",
            "transliteration": "Hiyye 'aadatan btitbokh il-ghada."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Expressing Frequency: Sometimes and Never"
        },
        "text": "For other frequencies, use أحياناً (aḥyānan - sometimes) and أبداً (abadan - never). Note that أبداً often requires a negative verb (ما verb).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا أحياناً بروح ع النادي.",
            "english": "I sometimes go to the gym.",
            "transliteration": "Ana aḥyānan barooḥ a'n-naadi."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هو أبداً ما بياكل لحمة.",
            "english": "He never eats meat.",
            "transliteration": "Huwa abadan ma byaakul laḥme."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
