    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Expressing Frequency: Every Day, Every Week"
        },
        "text": "To talk about activities that happen regularly, use كل يوم (kull yōm - every day) and كل أسبوع (kull usbū' - every week).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا بروح ع الشغل كل يوم.",
            "english": "I go to work every day.",
            "transliteration": "Ana barooḥ a'sh-shughl kull yōm."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هي بتزور أهلها كل أسبوع.",
            "english": "She visits her family every week.",
            "transliteration": "Hiyye btzoor ahlaha kull usbū'."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Expressing Your Daily Routine"
        },
        "text": "To refer to your daily schedule or routine, you can use برنامجي اليومي (barnāmejī l-yawmī - my daily program) or روتيني اليومي (rōtīnī l-yawmī - my daily routine).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "برنامجي اليومي كتير مشغول.",
            "english": "My daily program is very busy.",
            "transliteration": "Barnāmejī l-yawmī kteer mashghool."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "بحب روتيني اليومي.",
            "english": "I like my daily routine.",
            "transliteration": "Baḥibb rōtīnī l-yawmī."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
